Well - I went and - as I say, I seen a friend - I was really going to Fishlockes - for half-crown.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4790751 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid875679\charrsid5915590 What's Fishlockes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15492717 DD  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid875679\charrsid5915590 A florist. You know
, Fishlockes in town and that. And these - lady - and - I met one of my school friends and she was bit older than me and she'd gone and got taken on at Crawfords. I said, how much you getting there? She said, oh, four shillings. And you get sixpence if yo
u keep good time. Oh, said, I'm going. So I told mum and she said, what - you're not going there. I said, I am. I said, look you get more money. She said, I don't care, she said, I\rquote 
ve been and seen Mary - Mary McMurray. Like she was one of the head ones the
re. Used to do all the tables and - all that in those days, you know, for the big banquets - all that caper. Oh, she said, I'll have to go and tell her you're not going. Well I said, I'm going to Crawfords. And Crawfords I went and stuck there - forty-fiv
e years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4790751 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid875679\charrsid5915590 What did you do there?
